@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "PenDenTive" where
you want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other
files or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your
Workbench must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on any tile present on the board, if there is
one tile on top of it and one tile under, those tiles will exchange
their position. If there is only one tile, either over or under the
tile you clicked on, that tile will exchange its position with the
one you clicked on. Of course if there is no tile either under or
over the one you clicked on, nothing will happen.

  If 3 or more tiles of the same type are in line with each other,
those tiles will then be removed from the game board and you will
get points according to the number of tiles in that lineup:

  3 tiles give 1 point
  4 "  "  "  " 10 points
  5 "  "  "  " 100 points

  ...The fun begins when you make more than one alignment of tiles
of the same type, for example: if you make 2 alignments of 3 similar
tiles, you will get 1 point for each alignment, that total will be
added and the result will be multiplied by the number of
alignements, in this case: 2 points x 2 aligments = 4 points
total... As you can see, the amount of points earned can go up quite
a bit...

  However! If you make alignments of 3 or more tiles of the same
type, and there are tiles located under the tiles you lined up, as
the same type tiles will then be removed, the tiles located under
will "fall", as they will loose their "support", so to speak.
Every time that happens, you will be penalized in that the gauge
located at the right of the game board will rise according to the
amount of "lost" (or fallen) tiles... If that gauge fills up
completely, the game is over.

  Note that as the gauge is rising, it is normally coloured in blue,
if it gets coloured in red, watch out!...

  Another thing to watch for: when you click on tiles and no
alignment of at least 3 similar tiles are made, a new tile will
appear somewhere in the lower part of a suspended set of tiles.
Do not let the board fill up completely, because if that happens
the game will be over.

  Every time you make an alignment that gives you 100 points or
more, the gauge will lower a little... that is, if you do not let
10 tiles or more fall towards the bottom of the game board...!

  At the start of every game, 5 different types of tiles will
appear on the game board, as you progress in the game, new types
of tiles will appear...

  The main goal is to make aligments in the lowest parts of the
suspended tiles, as to not lose too many tiles at a time. If you
happen to clear the entire board, and you do not "bust" the lost
tiles gauge, the game will display a new board with more tiles,
and the game will continue.

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

@endnode

